	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>Monday</date> Evening <date>June 16&#47;56</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Again I trouble<lb/> you with &#8220;an effusion&#8221; drawn<lb/> from me by your holding<lb/> me up to the notice of the<lb/> orthodox in a bright light<lb/> reflecting on our most<lb/> venerable sages of blessed<lb/> memory.  I hope you<lb/> will be able to publish<lb/> it in the Occident for <date>July</date><lb/> as I am anxious to <hi rend="underline">right</hi><lb/> myself before the learned<lb/> and discriminating <hi rend="underline">readers</hi><lb/> &#40;including all the &#8220;Lions&#8221; of<lb/> the age&#41; of &#8220;The Occident&#8221;&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The article involves a grave<lb/> and momentous question<lb/> viz the Rabbinical authority&#41;</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>I trust the day will yet come<lb/> when the chaff shall be<lb/> separated from the wheat<lb/> and the latter alone preserved&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Now for the latest news&#33;<lb/>  Last <date>Shabat</date> the officiating<lb/> Parnass <persName>Saml Lazarus Esq</persName> felt<lb/> it his duty to send the<lb/> Shamas to <hi rend="underline">four</hi> young men<lb/> who were devoutly&#8212;&#8212;<lb/>talking&#44; <persName>Messrs Edmund H.</persName><lb/> <persName>Harman<add>&#63;</add></persName> <persName>Joshual H.</persName> &#38;<lb/> <persName>Mortimer H.</persName>  You can<lb/> imagine their indignation<lb/> upon the public reprimand<lb/> which they evinced by loud<lb/> words after school in the<lb/> vestibule.  They viewed<lb/> the affair as an <hi rend="underline">expression</hi> of<lb/> personal spite on the part<lb/> of the vice President&#33;</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>alleging that many others<lb/> older and wiser are allowed<lb/> to converse with impunity<lb/> while they were made <hi rend="underline">victims</hi><lb/> to personal and family hatred.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">One thing I do know and<lb/> can attest to&#44; many behave<lb/> shamefully with perfect<lb/> impunity.  Not that I approve<lb/> or justify indecorum in<lb/> a place that <hi rend="underline">should be</hi><lb/> considered sacred.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You are probably aware<lb/> to day two trustees were<lb/> elected&#44; in place of <persName>Messrs<lb/> B Nathan</persName> &#38; <persName>Simn Graham<add>&#63;</add></persName><lb/> the candidates were <persName>Messrs<lb/> Joe Soria</persName> and <persName>B. I. Hart</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I will endeavor to add<lb/> in a P. S. the result.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The weather is <hi rend="underline">getting</hi></p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>delightfully warm&#44; and this is<lb/> enough on this very interesting<lb/> topic&#33;  <persName>Mr Jeffn. Moise</persName><lb/> has been here some days<lb/> is thought very intelligent<lb/> and loquacious&#44; and by some<lb/> who probably do not understand<lb/> English&#44; pedantic&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">With remembrance to my<lb/> relatives&#44; I am dr sir yours<lb/> very Respectfully and sincerely</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">M Solomons</persName></p>
				<p><date>Tuesday</date> Morning &#61;<lb/> Please ask <persName>Aunt M&#39;s</persName><lb/> letter recd to day &#8212;<lb/> <persName>Messrs Soria</persName> &#38; <persName>Hart</persName><lb/> elected by a large<lb/> majority&#33;&#33;&#33;</p>
		</body>
